<dl id="n13055d"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n13" href="#n13055d">N13 (VI.D.3)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n13all.htm#n13055d"> 55(d)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> in prison garb</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Poor Wilde &hellip; to whom costume meant so much, suffered intensely from the hideous <mark>garb</mark> he was forced to wear in gaol &hellip; he stood for an hour on the platform at Clapham Junction <mark>in prison dress</mark> and handcuffed, the target of a jeering crowd. <small> Hester Travers Smith, <a name="HTS2" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#HTS2"><cite title="source">Psychic Messages from Oscar Wilde</cite></a> (Apr 1924) 160</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Raphael transcription: <a name="c04274d" href="c4all.htm#c04274d">VI.C.04:274(d)</a> </mm></dd> </dd></dl>
